comments: Schroder (LAL) brings his hands forward toward Irving's (DAL) midsection and marginal contact occurs as Irving drives toward the lane.

Replay review of the foul called on Gabriel (LAL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Gabriel jumps forward and delivers body contact that affects Irving's (DAL) driving shot attempt.
Schroder (LAL) extends his arms towards Kleber (DAL) during the screen but the contact is marginal.
Wood (DAL) and Gabriel (LAL) engage and disengage with one another during the rebound.
Gabriel (LAL) and Wood (DAL) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Davis (LAL) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Reaves (LAL) legally contests Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Irving (DAL) briefly has his arms around Davis' (LAL) midsection before correcting.
Davis (LAL) establishes himself in Irving's (DAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Irving (DAL) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Wood (DAL) moves forward slightly prior to marginal contact occurring with Davis' (LAL) upper half as they come together in the lane.
Wood (DAL) slightly extends his right arm outward prior to marginal contact occurring with Schroder's (LAL) right side as the screen is set during the inbound.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) extends his left arm forward and does not maintain a legal guarding position when contact occurs with Reaves' (LAL) arm during the rip-through.
Gabriel (LAL) is retreating toward the sideline while in Irving's (DAL) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together.
Reaves (LAL) initiates contact with Wood's (DAL) right arm and lower body, causing Wood to lose control of the ball as he starts his dribble.
Davis (LAL) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Wood (DAL) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Kleber (DAL) grasps and then quickly releases Davis' (LAL) left arm as Davis moves to set the pick.
Davis (LAL) and Hardaway Jr. (DAL) engage and disengage with one another following the expiration of the pick.
Kleber (DAL) moves toward Davis (LAL) as Davis cuts back into the lane and marginal body contact occurs when they come together after the release of the jump shot.

Wood (DAL) engages and disengages with Gabriel (LAL) as they each move to establish rebounding position. Wood and Gabriel then make incidental body contact with one another as they elevate to pursue the ball.
Schroder (LAL) moves forward slightly prior to marginal body contact occurring with Irving (DAL) as Irving passes.
Davis (LAL) initiates body contact with Kleber (DAL) during his jump shot attempt that affects his ability to return to the floor.
Green (DAL) commits a take foul on Davis (LAL).
Pinson (DAL) passes the ball within five seconds.
Gabriel (LAL) moves forward slightly prior to marginal contact occurring with Irving's (DAL) lower body as Irving receives the pass.
Kleber (DAL) establishes himself in Schroder's (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Irving (DAL) brings his off-arm outward slightly and marginal contact occurs with Schroder's (LAL) left arm during the drive.
Irving (DAL) establishes his left foot as his pivot and maintains it prior to releasing the pass.
Davis (LAL) legally contests Kleber's (DAL) jump shot attempt. After communicating with the Replay Center, it was confirmed that Kleber released the shot prior to the expiration of the game clock.
